mation, and the dangers in linking racial and national identities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCherokee IndiansxEthnic identity. 0aCherokee IndiansxMixed descent. 0aCherokee IndiansxSocial conditions. 0aEthnohistoryzOklahoma. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aamerica.  aamerican indians.  aanthropology.  ablood degree.  ablood ties.  acherokee culture.  acherokee indians.  acherokee nation.  acherokee studies.  acultural identity.  aethnography.  aethnohistory.  afederal government.  aindigenous peoples.  amodern history.  anational identity.  anative american culture.  anative americans.  anonfiction.  aoklahoma cherokee.  aoklahoma.  apolitical identity.  apolitical issues.  arace relations.  aracial blending.  aracial identification.  aracial identity.  aracial issues.  aracism.  asocial identity.  aunited states.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093608940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520936089423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520936089/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles